Heat the oil in a wok. Add the spring onion, bird's-eye chilli, chicken and soya beans to the wok and stir fry for three minutes.Add the noodles, soy sauce and orange juice to the wok and stir fry for a further 2-3 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.To serve, stir the sesame seeds and mint through the noodles and pile onto a plate.